title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that finds all the purchases in the household appliances file for purchases made in october 2025. It should only include purchases for organisation which have more than 10 departments, also return the creditor name of these purchases as well as the price and the purchase line. Output in a textfile.

operations.udf: (t: (org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record, Int)) => { val r = t._1; val orgId = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val creditorId = r.getField(3).asInstanceOf[Int]; val price = r.getField(8).asInstanceOf[Number]; val line = r.getField(7).toString; (creditorId, orgId, price, line) }

(t: ((Int, Int, Number, String), org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record)) => { val purchase = t._1; val creditorRec = t._2; val creditorName = creditorRec.getField(1).toString; val price = purchase._3; val line = purchase._4; s"${creditorName} | ${price} | ${line}" }

log.thoughts: Count departments per organisation, filter organisations with >10 departments, select purchases in October 2025, join with those organisations and creditor table, then output creditor name, price and line to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT department_id, organisation_id, name, operation_center, esyn FROM department) as X
(SELECT purchase_id, organisation_id, department_id, creditor_id, invoice_id, invoice_date, invoice_line_no, invoice_line_descr, invoice_line_price FROM factpurchases) as X

data.udf: (t: (org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record, Int)) => { val r = t._1; val orgId = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val creditorId = r.getField(3).asInstanceOf[Int]; val price = r.getField(8).asInstanceOf[Number]; val line = r.getField(7).toString; (creditorId, orgId, price, line) }

data.table: (SELECT creditor_id, name, creditor_type FROM creditor) as X

data.udf: (t: ((Int, Int, Number, String), org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record)) => { val purchase = t._1; val creditorRec = t._2; val creditorName = creditorRec.getField(1).toString; val price = purchase._3; val line = purchase._4; s"${creditorName} | ${price} | ${line}" }

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val f = r.getField(5); if(f == null) false else f.toString.startsWith("2025-10") }

(t: (org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record, Int)) => { val r = t._1; val orgId = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val creditorId = r.getField(3).asInstanceOf[Int]; val priceField = r.getField(8); val price = if(priceField == null) java.lang.Double.valueOf(0.0) else priceField.asInstanceOf[Number]; val lineField = r.getField(7); val line = if(lineField == null) "" else lineField.toString; (creditorId, orgId, price, line) }

(t: ((Int, Int, Number, String), org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record)) => { val purchase = t._1; val creditorRec = t._2; val creditorNameField = creditorRec.getField(1); val creditorName = if (creditorNameField == null) "" else creditorNameField.toString; val price = purchase._3; val line = purchase._4; s"${creditorName} | ${price} | ${line}" }

plan.thoughts: Guarded accesses to nullable Record fields: invoice_date, invoice_line_descr and invoice_line_price (and creditor name) to avoid NullPointerExceptions during toString/asInstanceOf.
